# Data Visualization using Charts in Excel

## Overview
This section demonstrates the creation and customization of charts in Excel for visualizing data.

---

## Tasks Performed

- Selected relevant data columns
- Used CTRL key to select non-adjacent columns (Name, Maths, Science)
- Created different types of charts:
  - Bar Chart (for comparison)
  - Pie Chart (for distribution)

---

## Customization

- Added chart titles
- Added axis labels
- Applied different chart styles
- Adjusted formatting for better readability

---

## Key Learnings

- Bar charts are useful for comparing values across categories
- Pie charts are useful for showing proportion of a whole
- Proper data selection is important for accurate visualization
- Customizing charts improves clarity and presentation

---

## Conclusion

This section provides a basic understanding of data visualization in Excel using charts and highlights how different chart types serve different purposes.
